title: Presidential Nominations Sent to the Senate, 5/13/10 | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House
Office of the Press Secretary


For Immediate Release
May 13, 2010

 



Presidential Nominations Sent to the Senate, 5/13/10




NOMINATIONS SENT TO THE SENATE:
Mark Feierstein, of Virginia, to be an Assistant Administrator of the United States Agency for International Development, vice Paul J. Bonicelli.
               
Osvaldo Luis Gratacós Munet, of Puerto Rico, to be Inspector General, Export-Import Bank, vice Michael W. Tankersley, resigned.
